-- U.K. Stocks Decline in London; Benchmark FTSE 100 Retreats 0.4 Percent
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-09-27T14:01:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/u-k-stocks-decline-in-london-benchmark-ftse-100-retreats-0-4-percent.html
U.K. stocks fell, led by a decline
in Smiths Group Plc and G4S Plc.  The FTSE 100 Index dropped 0.4 percent to 5,576.42 at 3:00
p.m. in London after swinging between gains and losses more than
10 times today.  Smiths Group dropped 2.4 percent to 1,197 pence as BofA-
Merrill Lynch Global Research downgraded the shares to
“neutral” from “buy.”  G4S, the world’s largest security company, also retreated,
falling 2.8  percent to 252.8 pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  